'County Mayo' () (Irish: Maigh Eo, meaning "Plain of the yew trees") is a county
in Ireland. It is located in the West Region, and it is also part of the
province of Connacht. It is named after the village of Mayo, which is now
generally known as Mayo Abbey. Mayo County Council is the local authority for
the county. The population of the county is 130,638 according to the 2011
census. The
boundaries of the county, which was formed in 1585, reflect the Mac William
